HEADWORD: Tilestone
<hw>Tile"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A kind of laminated shale or sandstone belonging
to some of the layers of the Upper Silurian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tile of stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilia</ent>⟦br⟧
